metadata.name: Go-PackCurd-Go 1/100000
metadata.description: Meet Pack Curd, the ultimate Wisconsin stereotype. He only wears the colors green, gold, or blaze orange. He's a cheesehead through and through, which basically means he's obsessed with Packer football, cold beer, and brats with kraut. On the weekends, you can find him tailgating the Frozen Tundra of Lambeau Field, or trying to perfect his cow-tipping craft. When he's not outside, he's inside watching the Packers, chanting "GO-PACK-GO", and drinking a beer, because Wisconsinites can't function without football and alcohol. As a dairy farmer, Pack Curd is no stranger to the smell of cow manure, and he loves nothing more than rolling down the windows of his ole' pickup and letting that wonderful aroma waft through. Then, when Oktoberfest rolls around, he pulls out his lederhosen and starts belting out "Roll Out the Barrel" at the top of his lungs, because that's just how WE do it in Wisconsin!
